You can custom backup options in the  node.backup  part of  config.conf , which looks like:  node.backup {
    # my priority, each member should use different priority
    priority = 
    # members should use same port
    port = 
    # peer's ip list, can't contain mine
    members = []
}  policy: 
1. the one which synchronized first will become master.
2. if synchronization is completed at the same time, the one which with big priority will become master.  E.g. create backups for node A(192.168.0.100) and node B(192.168.0.100 ):
node A's configuration:  node.backup {
    priority = 8 
    port = 10001
    members = [
        "192.168.0.101"
    ]
}  node B's configuration:  node.backup {
    priority = 5
    port = 10001
    members = [
        "192.168.0.100"
    ]
}  You may refer to the source code of  io.grpc.netty.NettyServerBuilder  class to see details or just make a decision according to the brief comments above.

